Education is the key to peace, stability and social cohesion, First Lady Margaret Kenyatta has said.&ldquo;No nation which allows its children to wilt in the shadow of neglect can ever hope to achieve peace and economic prosperity,&rdquo; she said last week.Kenyatta spoke during the sixth edition of the Murang&rsquo;a County Initiative scholarships and excellence awards ceremony at Ihura Stadium.Thirty-three students received full scholarships, and top-performing public primary schools from the eight subcounties of Murang&rsquo;a received trophies and cash prizes of Sh100,000 each.Teachers were also awarded. Kenyatta called for more investment in the education sector.